    "job_description": "Overview:\n\nRemote Angular Developer. US Employer, full time, work from anywhere.\n\nCompany Description:\n\nCosmogence is a platform that provides remote Angular Developer jobs that allow you to work from anywhere for companies in Canada and the United States.\n\nCosmogence is looking to fill remote Angular Developer jobs for our US based clients who are interested in hiring remote, full-time employees from around the world to be a part of their team. You should have a penchant for excellence with a proven track-record of successfully delivering high quality work, be a lifelong learner, have a positive attitude, be self-motivated, and have excellent English skills.\n\nThe specific tools and technologies, years of experience and job requirements will vary depending on the client you are hired by, so we are open to a variety of skill types and levels of experience. We’re looking for the best of the best–if you think that’s you, we encourage you to apply! Once you submit your profile, you will undergo our vetting process, and will be considered for a variety of clients. We will match you based on your interests, desired compensation, and their needs.\n\nJob Description:\n\nAs an Angular Developer, you will be responsible to write and test code, debugging programs and integrating applications with third-party web services. To be successful in this role, you should have experience using server-side logic and work well in a team. You will be a part of a creative team that is responsible for all aspects of the ongoing application development from the initial specification, through to developing, bug fix and launching.\n\nRequired Skills:\n• Bachelor’s/Master’s degree in Computer Science (or equivalent experience)\n• 3+ years of experience working with Angular (rare exceptions for highly skilled candidates)\n• Proficient in HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript\n• Write clean, efficient, and well-optimized code\n• Good knowledge of JavaScript MV-VM/MVC frameworks including Angular\n• Work with other developers to maintain workflow and integrate various components\n• Build compelling web applications using best practices of the AngularJS framework\n• Experience in writing cross-browser compatible code\n• Experience using JavaScript building tools (like Gulp, Grunt, etc.)\n• Working knowledge of database, APIs, proxies, caching layer, and other web services\n• Familiarity with RESTful services\n• Familiarity with back-end programming languages such as Java, .NET, Python, Ruby, etc.\n• Working knowledge of technologies such as AJAX and DOM manipulation techniques\n• Capability to implement AngularJS applications, directives, controllers, and services\n\nNice to have:\n• Experience with testing frameworks (e.g., Mocha, Jasmine, etc.)\n• Working knowledge of test runner tools (e.g., Karma, JEST, etc.)\n• Strong knowledge of source control systems (Git, Merging, Branching, Pull Requests, etc.)",
